{
  "name": "Water Release Great Shark Bullet",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Water.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You manipulate your water release chakra molding it until you manifest a single gargantuan shark that you then launch at a creature within range, leaving a trail of devastation in its path.</p><p>The shark is propelled in a straight line towards a single target creature. Make a Ranged Ninjutsu Attack. On a success they take cold damage equal to 10d8, and gain 2 ranks of Chilled.</p><p>All creatures the shark would pass through while traveling to the target creature would suffer some effect as well. All creatures except the target creature in a 15-foot wide, up to 120-foot line makes a Dexterity saving throw. The line ends early if the space the original target creature was occupying is less than 120 feet away from when the jutsu was cast. On a failed save they take 6d8 cold damage and 1 rank of chilled. Or half as much on a successful save and no additional effects.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above A-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 2d8.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
